#: includes/class-edg-statement.php:1125
msgid ""
"All links that open in a new tab/window announce this to screen reader users "
"via a hidden label."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-edg-statement.php:1129
msgid ""
"A skip navigation link is provided as the first element in the page, "
"allowing keyboard users to jump directly to the main content."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-edg-statement.php:1133
msgid ""
"Decorative images carry an explicit empty alt attribute so screen readers "
"skip them rather than announcing the file name."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-edg-statement.php:1137
msgid ""
"A visible, high-contrast focus indicator is applied to all interactive "
"elements for keyboard and switch access users."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-edg-statement.php:1141
msgid ""
"Navigation menus with sub-menus expose aria-haspopup and aria-expanded state "
"to assistive technologies."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-edg-statement.php:1145
msgid ""
"Content heading structure is validated on save to prevent level skips that "
"disorient screen reader users navigating by heading."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-edg-statement.php:1149
msgid ""
"Icon and image links without visible text receive programmatic accessible "
"labels so screen readers announce the link destination."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-edg-statement.php:1153
msgid ""
"Embedded iframes without a title attribute receive a programmatic title so "
"screen readers can identify the embedded content."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-edg-statement.php:1157
msgid ""
"Form inputs without a visible label receive programmatic labels so assistive "
"technology users can identify each field."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-edg-statement.php:1161
msgid ""
"WooCommerce quantity controls, product gallery, and cart notifications are "
"enhanced with ARIA labels and live region announcements."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-edg-statement.php:1165
msgid ""
"A pre-publish accessibility panel in the block editor alerts authors about "
"heading skips, missing alt text, and unlabeled form fields before content "
"goes live."
msgstr ""

